==Scottish Gaelic==

===Etymology===
Old Irish [[cloch]]

===Noun===
'''clach''' {{f}}, '''cloiche''' ''gen'', '''chloich''' ''dat'', '''clachan''' {{p}}
#a [[stone]], a [[rock]], a [[pebble]]
#''vulgar slang'', a [[testicle]]
#a stone weight (14 pounds)
#* clach olainn
#**a stone weight of wool
#[[monument]], [[memorial]]
#* clachan an cliù
#**the memorials of their fame

===Verb===
'''clach'''
#stone, strike with stones
#kill by stoning

